      "category": "ai",
      "title": "Claude Code uses Bun written in Rust now",
      "url": "https://simonwillison.net/2026/Jul/19/claude-code-in-bun-in-rust/",
      "discuss_url": "https://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=48966569",
      "score": 125,
      "comments": 163,
      "author": "tosh",
      "published": "2026-07-19T10:03:23Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Anthropic's agentic CLI, Claude Code, optimizes execution speed by integrating Bun and Rust for fast-startup terminal interactions.",
        "This transition reflects a broader shift toward compiling JS/TS-based AI developer tools into highly optimized, native binaries.",
        "Reducing local runtime latency is increasingly critical for sustaining low-overhead, iterative feedback loops in terminal-based AI agents."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
      "subsource": "lobste.rs/programming",
      "category": "engineering",
      "title": "Reviewing AI Code Is Not A Viable Argument",
      "url": "https://softwaremaxims.com/blog/reviewing-ai-code",
