      "score": 37,
      "comments": 85,
      "author": "Diana",
      "published": "2026-07-18T16:25:19Z",
      "bullets": [
        "Human code review fails to catch subtle LLM hallucinations and security bugs due to cognitive fatigue and automation bias.",
        "Reading code is harder than writing; LLMs shift the engineering bottleneck from creation to verification, increasing long-term technical debt.",
        "Engineers must implement automated CI/CD pipelines, unit testing, and static analysis instead of relying on manual PR reviews for AI-generated code."
      ]
    },
    {
      "source": "lobsters",
